### Role Mapping (Spec → Code)

| Spec Role | Mapped Code Role | Scope |
|-----------|-----------------|-------|
| Executive | `admin` (when `view=executive`) | Aggregate only |
| HR | `admin` | Full org access |
| Department Manager | `manager` | Own department only |
| Team Supervisor | `manager` (team scope) | Own team only |
| Data Analyst | `admin` (when `view=analyst`) | Full data + export |
| System Admin | `super_admin` | No analytics sections |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The existing codebase has 4 roles (`admin`, `manager`, `employee`, `super_admin`). I'll implement scope enforcement using [useAuth().role](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx#145-152) and the `user.department` field. The `super_admin` role will be blocked from analytics sections as specified.

